result.name: Palco Italian Ristorante Wanchai

reviews.text: Great food, great service, a bit pricey
Very good Italian food. Good service.
Good value for money, but a bit noisy

Palco is an Italian restaurant that is located in a non discrete building in Wan Chai. The pricing is a little bit on the high side but for Hong Kong it is fairly moderately priced. I came for the four course lunch set, which looks like a lot of food on paper but the portions are quite small. 

Food: 4 stars
Ambience/service: 4.5 stars
Value: 3.5 stars

The highlights of the meal were the pasta and the dessert. Although the portion was really small the pasta was cooked properly and seasoned well. The meat courses were disappointing as both the duck and the beef were a bit tough. If I were ordering a la carts I would stick with the pasta. 

The dessert was the best part of the meal. The dish was plated beautifully and there was a nice balance of textures and tastes. I really enjoyed the dessert.

Very nice food and services. The presentation is very French but the dishes are Italian. That makes very impressive. The 4course dinner for $500 while 6 for $700.  That make perfect sense after I had the 4 course but the amount may be a bit too small for adult man. The wine selection are very good. We chose a Pinot Noir but it went out of stock. In return, they recommended another bottle that is more fruity and full bodied. Which taste great. Again, just a bit pricey.
